I rec'd an email from IT with the following message

 

2015-11-30 10:38:34 EST - Sergey Kanishchev

Hi Lidia,
The system design is that an agent line (queue line) is recorded if agent is logged in.
If an agent is not logged in there should not be any calls to agent line and as result no calls for recording.

If you are receiving calls while CAD is not active it means these are personal calls and those will not be even in contact center call reporting if CAD is not active.

If you'd like to change system design please submit a service request to change Contact Center call recording design as it will impact all lines of business.
Thank you

Jane Osment's phone was tested (as an example) and all of her calls are being recorded on her CAD ext. whether she is logged into CAD or not. This is how we would like the entire call centre at Eco Select to funfction.

Please let Michelle Hetzler or I know if you have any questions.

Thanks,

Lidia Musca
